  "prompt": "How do I reschedule my appointment for passport because I put the wrong email?",
  "response": "To reschedule your passport appointment due to entering the wrong email address, follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Visit the Official Website**: Go to the website of the passport agency or authority that scheduled your appointment.\n\n2. **Locate the Appointment Section**: Look for a section related to appointments, often labeled as \u201cManage Appointment,\u201d \u201cReschedule Appointment,\u201d or something similar.\n\n3. **Log In or Access Your Appointment**: You may need to log in using your existing credentials. If you cannot log in due to the wrong email, look for an option to retrieve your appointment using other information (like your name and date of birth).\n\n4. **Contact Support**: If you can\u2019t access your appointment online, consider calling the support number provided on the website. Explain your situation, and they will guide you on how to proceed with rescheduling.\n\n5. **Check Your Email**: If the appointment confirmation was sent to the wrong email and you have access to that account, check for any links or instructions in the confirmation for rescheduling.\n\n6. **Provide Necessary Information**: When rescheduling, be prepared to provide any information they may need, such as your identification details and any confirmation number you received.\n\n7. **Confirm the New Appointment**: Once you successfully reschedule, ensure you receive a new confirmation email. If you still encounter issues, keep a copy of any correspondence or confirmation numbers for reference.\n\nIt's essential to act quickly, as appointment slots may fill up, especially if you're rescheduling closer to a deadline.",
